{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":980,"text":"It's easy to forget that last night,"},{"time":4203,"text":"one billion people went to sleep\nwithout access to electricity."},{"time":8094,"text":"One billion people."},{"time":10298,"text":"Two and a half billion people\ndid not have access to clean cooking fuels"},{"time":15553,"text":"or clean heating fuels."},{"time":18234,"text":"Those are the problems\nin the developing world."},{"time":20982,"text":"And it's easy for us not to be empathetic"},{"time":23642,"text":"with those people\nwho seem so distanced from us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26331,"text":"But even in our own world,\nthe developed world,"},{"time":29725,"text":"we see the tension of stagnant economies"},{"time":33234,"text":"impacting the lives of people around us."},{"time":36241,"text":"We see it in whole pieces of the economy,"},{"time":39813,"text":"where the people involved\nhave lost hope about the future"},{"time":43220,"text":"and despair about the present."},{"time":45457,"text":"We see that in the Brexit vote."},{"time":47546,"text":"We see that in the Sanders/Trump\ncampaigns in my own country."},{"time":51667,"text":"But even in countries as recently\nturning the corner"},{"time":56619,"text":"towards being in the developed world,"},{"time":58463,"text":"in China,"},{"time":59727,"text":"we see the difficulty\nthat President Xi has"},{"time":62700,"text":"as he begins to un-employ so many people\nin his coal and mining industries"},{"time":68214,"text":"who see no future for themselves."},{"time":71183,"text":"As we as a society\nfigure out how to manage"},{"time":74210,"text":"the problems of the developed world"},{"time":76187,"text":"and the problems of the developing world,"},{"time":78259,"text":"we have to look at how we move forward"},{"time":81131,"text":"and manage the environmental impact\nof those decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85868,"text":"We've been working on this problem\nfor 25 years, since Rio,"},{"time":88991,"text":"the Kyoto Protocols."},{"time":91223,"text":"Our most recent move is the Paris treaty,"},{"time":94514,"text":"and the resulting climate agreements"},{"time":97112,"text":"that are being ratified\nby nations around the world."},{"time":100045,"text":"I think we can be very hopeful"},{"time":102256,"text":"that those agreements,\nwhich are bottom-up agreements,"},{"time":105418,"text":"where nations have said\nwhat they think they can do,"},{"time":108303,"text":"are genuine and forthcoming\nfor the vast majority of the parties."},{"time":112977,"text":"The unfortunate thing"},{"time":115205,"text":"is that now, as we look\nat the independent analyses"},{"time":118756,"text":"of what those climate treaties\nare liable to yield,"},{"time":123083,"text":"the magnitude of the problem\nbefore us becomes clear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126965,"text":"This is the United States\nEnergy Information Agency's assessment"},{"time":131625,"text":"of what will happen if the countries\nimplement the climate commitments"},{"time":136337,"text":"that they've made in Paris"},{"time":138397,"text":"between now and 2040."},{"time":141221,"text":"It shows basically CO2 emissions\naround the world"},{"time":145465,"text":"over the next 30 years."},{"time":148236,"text":"There are three things that you need\nto look at and appreciate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152177,"text":"One, CO2 emissions are expected\nto continue to grow"},{"time":156372,"text":"for the next 30 years."},{"time":159265,"text":"In order to control climate,"},{"time":162054,"text":"CO2 emissions have to literally go to zero"},{"time":165564,"text":"because it's the cumulative emissions\nthat drive heating on the planet."},{"time":170445,"text":"This should tell you that we are losing\nthe race to fossil fuels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175567,"text":"The second thing you should notice"},{"time":177454,"text":"is that the bulk of the growth\ncomes from the developing countries,"},{"time":181771,"text":"from China, from India,\nfrom the rest of the world,"},{"time":184860,"text":"which includes South Africa\nand Indonesia and Brazil,"},{"time":189024,"text":"as most of these countries\nmove their people"},{"time":192353,"text":"into the lower range of lifestyles"},{"time":195288,"text":"that we literally take for granted\nin the developed world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200495,"text":"The final thing that you should notice"},{"time":202902,"text":"is that each year,"},{"time":205394,"text":"about 10 gigatons of carbon are getting\nadded to the planet's atmosphere,"},{"time":212994,"text":"and then diffusing into the ocean\nand into the land."},{"time":216011,"text":"That's on top of the 550 gigatons\nthat are in place today."},{"time":222062,"text":"At the end of 30 years,"},{"time":223920,"text":"we will have put 850 gigatons\nof carbon into the air,"},{"time":229171,"text":"and that probably goes a long way"},{"time":231446,"text":"towards locking in a 2-4 degree C increase\nin global mean surface temperatures,"},{"time":238140,"text":"locking in ocean acidification"},{"time":241227,"text":"and locking in sea level rise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244379,"text":"Now, this is a projection made by men"},{"time":248197,"text":"by the actions of society,"},{"time":250863,"text":"and it's ours to change, not to accept."},{"time":253912,"text":"But the magnitude of the problem\nis something we need to appreciate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258648,"text":"Different nations make\ndifferent energy choices."},{"time":261115,"text":"It's a function\nof their natural resources."},{"time":263466,"text":"It's a function of their climate."},{"time":265499,"text":"It's a function of the development path\nthat they've followed as a society."},{"time":270664,"text":"It's a function of where\non the surface of the planet they are."},{"time":274191,"text":"Are they where it's dark\na lot of the time,"},{"time":276715,"text":"or are they at the mid-latitudes?"},{"time":278989,"text":"Many, many, many things\ngo into the choices of countries,"},{"time":283185,"text":"and they each make a different choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286878,"text":"The overwhelming thing\nthat we need to appreciate"},{"time":290064,"text":"is the choice that China has made."},{"time":292695,"text":"China has made the choice,"},{"time":295313,"text":"and will make the choice, to run on coal."},{"time":298358,"text":"The United States has an alternative."},{"time":300401,"text":"It can run on natural gas"},{"time":302182,"text":"as a result of the inventions\nof fracking and shale gas,"},{"time":306031,"text":"which we have here."},{"time":307526,"text":"They provide an alternative."},{"time":310662,"text":"The OECD Europe has a choice."},{"time":313881,"text":"It has renewables that it can afford\nto deploy in Germany"},{"time":316974,"text":"because it's rich enough\nto afford to do it."},{"time":319615,"text":"The French and the British\nshow interest in nuclear power."},{"time":325702,"text":"Eastern Europe, still very heavily\ncommitted to natural gas and to coal,"},{"time":330331,"text":"and with natural gas\nthat comes from Russia,"},{"time":333083,"text":"with all of its entanglements."},{"time":335558,"text":"China has many fewer choices"},{"time":338039,"text":"and a much harder row to hoe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341557,"text":"If you look at China, and you ask yourself"},{"time":344613,"text":"why has coal been important to it,"},{"time":346841,"text":"you have to remember what China's done."},{"time":349534,"text":"China brought people to power,\nnot power to people."},{"time":353380,"text":"It didn't do rural electrification."},{"time":356427,"text":"It urbanized."},{"time":357954,"text":"It urbanized by taking low-cost labor\nand low-cost energy,"},{"time":362182,"text":"creating export industries"},{"time":364123,"text":"that could fund a tremendous\namount of growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367535,"text":"If we look at China's path,"},{"time":369763,"text":"all of us know that prosperity in China\nhas dramatically increased."},{"time":374713,"text":"In 1980, 80 percent of China's population"},{"time":379283,"text":"lived below the extreme poverty level,"},{"time":382493,"text":"below the level of having\n$1.90 per person per day."},{"time":386658,"text":"By the year 2000, only 20 percent\nof China's population"},{"time":392154,"text":"lived below the extreme poverty level --"},{"time":395498,"text":"a remarkable feat,"},{"time":397977,"text":"admittedly, with some costs\nin civil liberties"},{"time":400368,"text":"that would be tough to accept\nin the Western world."},{"time":404548,"text":"But the impact of all that wealth"},{"time":407479,"text":"allowed people to get\nmassively better nutrition."},{"time":411484,"text":"It allowed water pipes to be placed."},{"time":414223,"text":"It allowed sewage pipes to be placed,"},{"time":416706,"text":"dramatic decrease in diarrheal diseases,"},{"time":420590,"text":"at the cost of some outdoor air pollution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424070,"text":"But in 1980, and even today,"},{"time":426374,"text":"the number one killer in China\nis indoor air pollution,"},{"time":430833,"text":"because people do not have access\nto clean cooking and heating fuels."},{"time":436066,"text":"In fact, in 2040,"},{"time":439794,"text":"it's still estimated\nthat 200 million people in China"},{"time":444593,"text":"will not have access\nto clean cooking fuels."},{"time":449133,"text":"They have a remarkable path to follow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452854,"text":"India also needs to meet the needs\nof its own people,"},{"time":457626,"text":"and it's going to do that by burning coal."},{"time":460475,"text":"When we look at the EIA's projections\nof coal burning in India,"},{"time":466591,"text":"India will supply nearly four times\nas much of its energy from coal"},{"time":471518,"text":"as it will from renewables."},{"time":474962,"text":"It's not because they don't know\nthe alternatives;"},{"time":477839,"text":"it's because rich countries\ncan do what they choose,"},{"time":482162,"text":"poor countries do what they must."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486198,"text":"So what can we do to stop\ncoal's emissions in time?"},{"time":490899,"text":"What can we do that changes\nthis forecast that's in front of us?"},{"time":495535,"text":"Because it's a forecast that we can change\nif we have the will to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501094,"text":"First of all, we have to think\nabout the magnitude of the problem."},{"time":504537,"text":"Between now and 2040,"},{"time":507104,"text":"800 to 1,600 new coal plants\nare going to be built around the world."},{"time":514085,"text":"This week, between one and three\none-gigawatt coal plants"},{"time":518718,"text":"are being turned on around the world."},{"time":521817,"text":"That's happening regardless\nof what we want,"},{"time":525891,"text":"because the people\nthat rule their countries,"},{"time":528423,"text":"assessing the interests of their citizens,"},{"time":530817,"text":"have decided it's in the interest\nof their citizens to do that."},{"time":535335,"text":"And that's going to happen\nunless they have a better alternative."},{"time":539726,"text":"And every 100 of those plants will use up"},{"time":543507,"text":"between one percent and three percent"},{"time":546662,"text":"of the Earth's climate budget."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549264,"text":"So every day that you go home\nthinking that you should do something"},{"time":552779,"text":"about global warming,"},{"time":554594,"text":"at the end of that week, remember:"},{"time":556550,"text":"somebody fired up a coal plant\nthat's going to run for 50 years"},{"time":560967,"text":"and take away your ability to change it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565972,"text":"What we've forgotten is something\nthat Vinod Khosla used to talk about,"},{"time":569590,"text":"a man of Indian ethnicity\nbut an American venture capitalist."},{"time":573339,"text":"And he said, back in the early 2000s,"},{"time":576188,"text":"that if you needed to get\nChina and India off of fossil fuels,"},{"time":580219,"text":"you had to create a technology\nthat passed the \"Chindia test,\""},{"time":584640,"text":"\"Chindia\" being the appending\nof the two words."},{"time":587900,"text":"It had to be first of all viable,"},{"time":590283,"text":"meaning that technically, they could\nimplement it in their country,"},{"time":593901,"text":"and that it would be accepted\nby the people in the country."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598191,"text":"Two, it had to be a technology\nthat was scalable,"},{"time":604788,"text":"that it could deliver the same benefits"},{"time":607830,"text":"on the same timetable as fossil fuels,"},{"time":611387,"text":"so that they can enjoy the kind of life,\nagain, that we take for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615766,"text":"And third, it had to be cost-effective"},{"time":618299,"text":"without subsidy or without mandate."},{"time":621432,"text":"It had to stand on its own two feet;"},{"time":624170,"text":"it could not be maintained\nfor that many people"},{"time":628073,"text":"if in fact, those countries\nhad to go begging"},{"time":631009,"text":"or had some foreign country say,\n\"I won't trade with you,\""},{"time":635328,"text":"in order to get\nthe technology shift to occur."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640168,"text":"If you look at the Chindia test,"},{"time":641878,"text":"we simply have not come up\nwith alternatives that meet that test."},{"time":646984,"text":"That's what the EIA forecast tells us."},{"time":650765,"text":"China's building 800 gigawatts of coal,"},{"time":654866,"text":"400 gigawatts of hydro,"},{"time":657772,"text":"about 200 gigawatts of nuclear,"},{"time":660501,"text":"and on an energy-equivalent basis,\nadjusting for intermittency,"},{"time":664586,"text":"about 100 gigawatts of renewables."},{"time":667554,"text":"800 gigawatts of coal."},{"time":669805,"text":"They're doing that, knowing the costs\nbetter than any other country,"},{"time":673381,"text":"knowing the need better\nthan any other country."},{"time":676454,"text":"But that's what they're aiming for in 2040"},{"time":679105,"text":"unless we give them a better choice."},{"time":682199,"text":"To give them a better choice,"},{"time":683663,"text":"it's going to have to meet\nthe Chindia test."}]},{"cues":[{"time":686248,"text":"If you look at all the alternatives\nthat are out there,"},{"time":688930,"text":"there are really two\nthat come near to meeting it."},{"time":691865,"text":"First is this area of new nuclear\nthat I'll talk about in just a second."},{"time":696107,"text":"It's a new generation of nuclear plants\nthat are on the drawing boards"},{"time":699431,"text":"around the world,"},{"time":700731,"text":"and the people who are\ndeveloping these say"},{"time":703093,"text":"we can get them\nin position to demo by 2025"},{"time":707252,"text":"and to scale by 2030,\nif you will just let us."},{"time":711246,"text":"The second alternative\nthat could be there in time"},{"time":714771,"text":"is utility-scale solar\nbacked up with natural gas,"},{"time":718500,"text":"which we can use today,"},{"time":720248,"text":"versus the batteries\nwhich are still under development."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724589,"text":"So what's holding new nuclear back?"},{"time":727686,"text":"Outdated regulations\nand yesterday's mindsets."},{"time":731972,"text":"We have not used our latest\nscientific thinking on radiological health"},{"time":736191,"text":"to think how we communicate\nwith the public"},{"time":738903,"text":"and govern the testing\nof new nuclear reactors."},{"time":741729,"text":"We have new scientific knowledge\nthat we need to use"},{"time":745950,"text":"in order to improve the way\nwe regulate nuclear industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750872,"text":"The second thing is we've got a mindset"},{"time":753345,"text":"that it takes 25 years\nand 2 to 5 billion dollars"},{"time":756178,"text":"to develop a nuclear power plant."},{"time":757937,"text":"That comes from the historical,\nmilitary mindset"},{"time":762443,"text":"of the places nuclear power came from."},{"time":765356,"text":"These new nuclear ventures are saying"},{"time":767591,"text":"that they can deliver power\nfor 5 cents a kilowatt hour;"},{"time":771212,"text":"they can deliver it\nfor 100 gigawatts a year;"},{"time":774543,"text":"they can demo it by 2025;"},{"time":777168,"text":"and they can deliver it in scale by 2030,"},{"time":780634,"text":"if only we give them a chance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":784064,"text":"Right now, we're basically\nwaiting for a miracle."},{"time":787888,"text":"What we need is a choice."},{"time":789952,"text":"If they can't make it safe,\nif they can't make it cheap,"},{"time":792780,"text":"it should not be deployed."},{"time":794621,"text":"But what I want you to do\nis not carry an idea forward,"},{"time":798699,"text":"but write your leaders,"},{"time":800374,"text":"write the head of the NGOs you support,"},{"time":802776,"text":"and tell them to give you the choice,"},{"time":806290,"text":"not the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807465,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":808673,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}